        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "The hierarchy of efficiency gains: "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "FlashAttention gives the biggest free speedup — enable it first. GQA / MQA give the biggest memory reduction for inference — adopt them when KV cache is the bottleneck. Sparse and linear attention change the model's inductive bias and require training from scratch; use them only when the sequence lengths truly cannot fit in standard attention at all."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
